flowchart TD

    %% ── STEP 1: Start ──────────────────────────────────────────────
    A([🚀 You want to check\nif a Docker image is safe])
    A --> B[Open the Security Dashboard\nin your web browser]

    %% ── STEP 2: Pick what to scan ──────────────────────────────────
    B --> C{Which image\ndo you want to scan?}
    C -->|Type an image name\ne.g. nginx or ubuntu| D[Type the image name\nand press Scan]
    C -->|Pick from the list\nof images on your computer| E[Select a local image\nfrom the dropdown]

    %% ── STEP 3: The system checks the image ────────────────────────
    D --> F[The system fetches\nthe image from the internet\nif not already downloaded]
    E --> F
    F --> G[Trivy security tool\nscans every file inside\nthe image for known problems]

    %% ── STEP 4: Were any problems found? ───────────────────────────
    G --> H{Were any security\nproblems found?}

    %% ── STEP 4a: No problems ────────────────────────────────────────
    H -->|No problems found| I[✅ Great news!\nThe image looks safe]
    I --> J[Results are saved\nso you can look back\nat them later]

    %% ── STEP 4b: Problems found ─────────────────────────────────────
    H -->|Yes, problems found| K[Problems are sorted\nby how dangerous they are]

    K --> L{How serious\nare they?}
    L -->|🔴 CRITICAL or 🟠 HIGH| M[⚠️ A Slack alert is sent\nto the security team\nright away]
    L -->|🟡 MEDIUM or 🔵 LOW| N[Problems are logged\nfor review later]

    M --> O[Results are saved\nto the database]
    N --> O

    %% ── STEP 5: View the results on screen ─────────────────────────
    J --> P[Dashboard shows\na summary of the scan]
    O --> P

    P --> Q[You can see:\n• Total problems found\n• A chart by severity\n• A history of all scans]

    %% ── STEP 6: Download a report ───────────────────────────────────
    Q --> R{Do you need\na report to share?}
    R -->|Yes, as PDF| S[📄 Download PDF report]
    R -->|Yes, as Excel| T[📊 Download Excel report]
    R -->|No, just browsing| U([✔️ Done — stay on dashboard])

    S --> U
    T --> U

    %% ── STEP 7: Automatic daily scan ───────────────────────────────
    V([🕑 Every day at 2 AM\nGitHub Actions runs automatically])
    V --> W[It scans the project's\nown Docker image]
    W --> X{Any CRITICAL\nproblems found?}
    X -->|Yes| Y[🚨 GitHub Actions\nflags the build as failed\nand notifies the team]
    X -->|No| Z[✅ Build passes\nAll clear for today]

    %% ── Styling ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    style A fill:#4CAF50,color:#fff,stroke:#388E3C
    style I fill:#4CAF50,color:#fff,stroke:#388E3C
    style U fill:#4CAF50,color:#fff,stroke:#388E3C
    style Z fill:#4CAF50,color:#fff,stroke:#388E3C
    style M fill:#FF5722,color:#fff,stroke:#BF360C
    style Y fill:#FF5722,color:#fff,stroke:#BF360C
    style V fill:#1976D2,color:#fff,stroke:#0D47A1
